In preparing the system capacity development strategy, the cabinet shall solicit and consider public comment on, and incorporate into the strategy as appropriate:
The methods or criteria that the cabinet will use to identify and prioritize public water systems most in need of improving technical, financial, and managerial capacity;
A description of the institutional, regulatory, financial, tax, or legal factors at the federal, state, or local level that encourage or impair system capacity development;
A description of how the cabinet will use the authorities and resources of the Safe Drinking Water Act as amended by PL 104-182, or other means, to assist public water systems in complying with national primary drinking water regulations, to encourage the development of partnerships between public water systems to enhance the system capacity of public water systems, and to assist public water systems in the training and certification of operators;
A description of how the cabinet will establish a baseline against which to measure improvements in system capacity with respect to national primary drinking water regulations, this chapter, KRS 224.10-110, and administrative regulations promulgated thereunder; and
An identification of the persons that have an interest in and are involved in the development and implementation of the system capacity development strategy, including all appropriate agencies of federal, state, and local governments, private and nonprofit public water systems, and public water system customers.
